## Frequently Asked Questions

### Can I self-host PlexMCP for my company?

**Yes!** Self-hosting for your own organization's internal use is always permitted, regardless of your company's revenue.

### Does this apply to organizations under $1M revenue?

No. Organizations with less than $1M annual revenue can use PlexMCP for any purpose except operating a competing hosted service.

### What counts as "competing"?

Only offering a hosted MCP gateway service substantially similar to PlexMCP Cloud. Building products that use MCPs, integrating with PlexMCP, or self-hosting are not competing uses.

### When does this become fully open source?

On January 6, 2031, this license automatically converts to Apache 2.0, making the Software fully open source with no restrictions.

### How do I get a commercial license?

Contact sales@plexmcp.com with your requirements.
